<reference id="reference_ntt_lkg_pvb">
    <?oxy_comment_start author="erica_txone" timestamp="20221205T161814+0800" comment="ask TC for update"?>
    <title>Configuration for Silent Installation</title><?oxy_comment_end?>
    <refbody>
        <section id="section_q2x_4kg_pvb">
            <p><indexterm>silent installation<indexterm>configuration</indexterm></indexterm>Users
                can pre-define the setup configuration for installation. The name is fixed to <ph
                    conkeyref="PRODvars/SETUP_FILE"/>. The launcher will parse <ph
                    conkeyref="PRODvars/SETUP_FILE"/> while executing. You can find <ph
                    conkeyref="PRODvars/SETUP_FILE"/> in the installation folder as shown below:<fig
                    id="fig_zhn_5kg_pvb">
                    <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>
                    <title>Installer Folder</title><?oxy_custom_end?>
                </fig></p>
        </section>
        <section id="section_zlf_1lg_pvb">
            <title>An Example of the Configuration File for Silent Installation</title>
            <p>See below as the example of the defined configuration file. You can define your own
                configuration settings by changing the values.<note id="note_rm5_kng_pvb">
                    <ul id="ul_u2s_2yg_pvb">
                        <li>
                            <p>Specify the
                                <?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>license
                                key<?oxy_custom_end?> and password, and then enable silent
                                installation by changing the <codeph>enable_silent_install</codeph>
                                value to <codeph>true</codeph> in the configuration file. If you
                                would like to manage the agent using StellarOne, please configure
                                the server session host value with the server IP address.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            <p>If you use a license file for license activation, ensure the file
                                extension is <filepath>.txt</filepath> and place it as the top-level
                                file in the installer package, and then specify the value of the
                                product serial number in the <ph conkeyref="PRODvars/SETUP_FILE"/>
                                file.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </note></p>
            <?oxy_comment_start author="erica_txone" timestamp="20221206T095841+0800" comment="take a screenshot or by typing?"?>
            <p><b><?oxy_custom_start type="oxy_content_highlight" color="255,255,0"?>Example:<?oxy_custom_end?></b></p><?oxy_comment_end?>
            <note id="note_bs3_31d_tvb">
                <p>(Optional) Insert a line under the <codeph>install</codeph> section. Type
                        <userinput>bypass_windefend_check: true</userinput> The endpoint will bypass
                    checking Windows Defender status to get the <ph
                        conkeyref="PRODvars/PRODUCT_SP_ALTERNATIVE_NAME">OFFICIAL_PRODUCT_NAME</ph>
                    installed without disabling Windows Defender.</p>
            </note>
        </section>
        <section id="section_l3d_krc_tvb">
            <title>Parameters of the Configuration File for Silent Installation</title>
            <p>The following table lists parameters for <ph conkeyref="PRODvars/INSTALLER"/> along
                with the details of their use. </p>
        </section>
